PERTH (miningweekly.com) â€“ ASX-listed Aeris Resources has tipped a 4% increase in full year production expectations on the back of strong production performances at its Tritton and Murrawombie underground mines, along with higher copper grades in New South Wales. The miner on Thursday advised that its copper production guidance for 2019 had now increased to between 26 450 t and 26 650 t, up from the previous guidance of 25 500 t made in April this year. The new production target is also 8% higher than the original guidance of 24 500 t.